"The Infinite Square Well (Particle in a Box) is the simplest quantum system. Because the walls are infinitely high, the wavefunction must be exactly zero at the boundaries. This boundary condition forces the allowed states (eigenstates) to be standing waves with quantized energy levels proportional to n^2. A Gaussian wavepacket placed inside will bounce back and forth, interfering with its own reflection to create complex, temporary fractal patterns before eventually undergoing quantum revival." = "无限深方形势阱（盒子中的粒子）是最简单的量子系统。因为势阱壁无限高，波函数在边界处必须严格为零。这种边界条件迫使允许的量子态（本征态）成为能量正比于 n^2 的驻波。置于其中的高斯波包会来回反弹，与自身的反射波发生干涉，在最终经历量子复苏（Quantum Revival）之前，会形成极其复杂的瞬态分形图案。";
"The Kronig-Penney model demonstrates electrons moving through a crystal lattice. The periodic arrangement of barriers creates energy bands and gaps. If the particle energy falls into a conduction band, it will travel through the entire lattice almost freely, despite the barriers. If it falls into a band gap, it will suffer Bragg reflection and be completely repelled." = "克罗尼格-彭尼模型展示了电子穿过晶格的运动。势垒的周期性排列创造了能带和禁带。如果粒子的能量落在导带中，尽管有势垒阻挡，它几乎可以自由地穿过整个晶格。如果它落在禁带中，它将遭受布拉格反射并被完全排斥回来。";
"The Quantum Harmonic Oscillator is one of the most important models in physics because any smooth potential well looks harmonic near its minimum. A coherent state (a displaced Gaussian wavepacket) will oscillate back and forth perfectly without changing its shape, mimicking classical motion. However, if you \"squeeze\" or \"stretch\" the initial packet (by changing the mass or adding custom momentum), you will see the wavepacket \"breathe\" as it oscillates, trading spatial uncertainty for momentum uncertainty." = "量子谐振子是物理学中最重要的模型之一，因为任何平滑的势阱在其最小值附近看起来都像是谐振子。相干态（位移的高斯波包）将完美地来回振荡而不改变其形状，模仿经典运动。但是，如果您“挤压”或“拉伸”初始波包（通过改变质量或添加自定义动量），您会看到波包在振荡时“呼吸”，用位置不确定性交换动量不确定性。";
"The attractive well can temporarily capture parts of the wavepacket or cause multiple internal reflections." = "吸引势阱可以暂时捕获部分波包或引起多次内部反射。";
"The attractive well pulls the wavepacket inward. Depending on the impact parameter, it causes angular deflection, and part of the probability may be temporarily captured in resonance states." = "吸引势阱将波包向内拉。根据碰撞参数的不同，它会引起角偏转，部分概率可能暂时被捕获在共振态中。";
"The barrier reshapes the packet into reflected and transmitted wavefronts." = "势垒将波包重塑为反射波前和透射波前。";
"The circular boundary acts as a mirror, reflecting the wavepacket back toward the center and creating intricate interference ripples." = "圆形边界就像一面镜子，将波包反射回中心，产生错综复杂的干涉波纹。";
"The double well potential is a classic model for quantum tunneling and spontaneous symmetry breaking. If a particle starts purely in one well, it is not in an energy eigenstate. Instead, it is a superposition of the symmetric (lower energy) and antisymmetric (higher energy) ground states. The phase difference between these states evolves over time, causing the probability density to slowly \"leak\" through the barrier and slosh back and forth. This is known as Rabi oscillation. Try the \"Symmetric Tunneling\" preset and hit play, or try \"Asymmetric Localization\" by making the right well much wider." = "双势阱是量子隧穿和自发对称性破缺的经典模型。如果粒子纯粹从一个势阱开始，它不处于能量本征态。相反，它是对称（较低能量）和反对称（较高能量）基态的叠加。这些状态之间的相位差随时间演化，导致概率密度缓慢地穿过势垒并在两端来回振荡。这被称为拉比振荡。尝试“对称隧穿”预设并点击播放，或者尝试通过使右侧势阱更宽来观察“不对称局域化”。";
"The double-slit experiment is the quintessential demonstration of wave-particle duality. When a coherent wavepacket arrives at the barrier, the two slits act as secondary point sources. As these two new waves expand, their peaks and troughs overlap, creating regions of constructive interference (bright fringes) and destructive interference (dark nodes). Notice how changing the initial momentum (wavelength) or slit separation alters the fringe spacing." = "双缝实验是波粒二象性的经典演示。当相干波包到达势垒时，两条狭缝充当次级点波源。随着这两个新波扩展，它们的波峰和波谷重叠，形成了相长干涉（亮条纹）和相消干涉（暗节点）区域。注意观察改变初始动量（波长）或狭缝间距如何改变干涉条纹的间距。";
"The drawn curve becomes the potential energy landscape." = "绘制的曲线将成为势能曲面。";
"The exact stationary states for this linear potential are described by Airy functions." = "这种线性势能下的精确稳态由艾里函数描述。";
"The packet center oscillates in the quadratic trap." = "波包中心在二次势阱中振荡。";
"The packet reflects from the high wall while probability remains inside the box." = "波包从高墙反射，同时概率总和保持在盒子内。";
"The packet splits into reflected and transmitted components." = "波包分裂成反射和透射两个分量。";
"The regularized Coulomb potential captures the wavepacket, similar to how a nucleus binds an electron." = "正则化库仑势捕获波包，类似于原子核束缚电子。";
"The total probability should stay near one while the packet moves." = "当波包移动时，总概率应保持在 1 附近。";
"The two openings create overlapping probability amplitudes downstream." = "两个开口在下游产生重叠的概率振幅。";
"The wavepacket splits into a reflected and a transmitted wave when the energy exceeds the step height." = "当能量超过势阶高度时，波包分裂为反射波和透射波。";
"The wavepacket undergoes periodic motion in both X and Y directions, creating Lissajous-like trajectories." = "波包在 X 和 Y 方向都经历周期性运动，形成类似李萨如 (Lissajous) 的轨迹。";
"This experiment visualizes quantum tunneling and reflection. When a particle encounters a finite potential barrier, classical mechanics dictates it will bounce back if its energy is less than the barrier height. In quantum mechanics, the wavefunction decays exponentially inside the barrier but does not immediately drop to zero. If the barrier is thin enough, a transmitted wave emerges on the other side. Try the \"Deep Tunneling\" preset to see a small fraction of the wave survive the barrier." = "此实验可视化了量子隧穿和反射。当粒子遇到有限势垒时，经典力学规定如果其能量小于势垒高度，它将被弹回。在量子力学中，波函数在势垒内部呈指数衰减，但不会立即降为零。如果势垒足够薄，透射波将在另一侧出现。尝试“深层隧穿”预设以观察少量波穿越势垒。";
"Tight Squeeze" = "狭窄空间";
"Total Reflection (Thick Barrier)" = "全反射 (厚势垒)";
"Total energy should stay nearly flat for a fixed Hamiltonian." = "对于固定的哈密顿量，总能量应保持几乎不变。";
"Undo Draw" = "撤销绘图";
"Unlike a classical ball, the quantum wavepacket spreads out and its different components interfere as they bounce against the hard floor, creating complex interference patterns." = "与经典小球不同，量子波包会散开，其不同分量在坚硬的地板上弹跳时会发生干涉，从而产生复杂的干涉图样。";
"Unlike a perfect harmonic oscillator, the Morse potential is repulsive near the origin (atoms colliding) but flattens out at long distances (dissociation)." = "与完美的谐振子不同，莫尔斯势能在原点附近（原子碰撞）是排斥的，但在长距离处变得平缓（解离）。";
"Unlike the infinite well, the walls here have a finite energy height. This means the wavefunction does not abruptly drop to zero at the edges; instead, it penetrates into the classically forbidden region (the walls) with exponential decay. If the well is shallow or the particle has high energy, it can escape. Notice how the wavepacket leaks outside the well boundaries during reflections." = "与无限深势阱不同，这里的势阱壁具有有限的能量高度。这意味着波函数在边缘不会突然降为零，而是以指数衰减的方式穿透到经典力学上的禁区（势阱壁内）。如果势阱很浅或者粒子具有高能量，它就可以逃逸。注意观察波包在反射过程中是如何“渗漏”到势阱边界之外的。";
